chat_history.content:
J.K. Rowling's most popular book series is Harry Potter, which follows the adventures of a young wizard named Harry Potter and his friends as they navigate their education at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry while facing off against the dark wizard Lord Voldemort and his followers. 

The main characters in the series are:
- Harry Potter - The series' protagonist, an orphan who discovers he is a wizard and embarks on a journey to defeat Voldemort.
- Ron Weasley - Harry's best friend, a loyal and courageous red-headed wizard.
- Hermione Granger - A brilliant and resourceful witch who becomes friends with Harry and Ron.
- Albus Dumbledore - The wise and powerful wizard who serves as the headmaster of Hogwarts and a mentor to Harry.
- Lord Voldemort - The dark wizard who killed Harry's parents and is the series' main antagonist.
- Severus Snape - A complex and conflicted character who is a double agent, working for both Lord Voldemort and the good side.
- Draco Malfoy - A rival and antagonist to Harry, also a wizard, who is a member of the wealthy and influential Malfoy family.
- Professor McGonagall - A teacher and transfiguration expert at Hogwarts, she is a mentor to Harry and a loyal member of the good side.
- Rubeus Hagrid - The half-giant, half-human gamekeeper at Hogwarts, loyal to Harry and a kind-hearted friend.
- Neville Longbottom - Another student at Hogwarts who becomes a close friend of Harry's.
- Ginny Weasley - Ron's younger sister, who eventually becomes Harry's wife.

Would you like to know more about the Harry Potter series or any of these characters?

- Ron Weasley: March 1st
- Hermione Granger: September 19th (or September 12th in some sources)

Please note that these dates are based on information from fan sources and may not be verified as official canon.

Harry Potter, the protagonist of J.K. Rowling's most popular book series, was born on July 31st. His best friend and loyal companion, Ron Weasley, was born on March 1st. Another close friend, Hermione Granger, has her birthday on September 19th, though some sources state it's September 12th. Neville Longbottom, who becomes a close friend of Harry's, was born on July 30th. Draco Malfoy, Harry's rival and an antagonist in the series, has his birthday on June 5th. 

The Harry Potter series follows these characters as they navigate their education at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, facing off against the dark wizard Lord Voldemort and his followers. Along with these main characters, the series also features Albus Dumbledore, the wise headmaster of Hogwarts, and Severus Snape, a complex double agent. Additionally, there are other important characters like Professor McGonagall, a transfiguration expert and mentor to Harry, and Rubeus Hagrid, the half-giant, half-human gamekeeper, who is loyal to Harry and his friends.

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.
